If I had to imagine what the dining experience would have been like a couple of decades ago for the first and second generation Italian families living in middle America it would probably look something like Christos.
The place has that ambiance and charm that say's "You're Family"....sorry Olive Garden.
The food is good and while there are other Italian places in town that are arguably better in quality and taste, none of them really beat this place in terms of authentic Italiian-American atmosphere.
The place is up there with Durant's, Monti's, and TeePee's as essential Phoenix dining landmarks.

