A large group (17) of us came in for NYE and it was fabulous as always.
We started off with a bunch of appetizers for the table followed by soup then salad.
The soup that evening was some sort of mushroom, artichoke, potato combination that was out of this world and if anyone has the recipe, please send it to me!
The salad was the same as always, nothing spectacular but it serves the purpose.
On to the entrees, they had a prix-fixe menu as they do for all major holidays.
There were A LOT of seafood options, but no vegetarian (they were able to accommodate but it wasn't listed) and only one chicken option.
I was hoping to see at least 2 chicken options for those of us who don't love breaded chicken.
There were also a lot of beef and pork options.
The chicken was similar to a Cordon Bleu without the ham, served with gnocchi and some sort of cheese sauce on top.
I loved it but others in the party didn't care for it as much as some of the other options you can get when it's not a holiday.
We then finished with desert.
Service was wonderful, the food was great and we will definitely be back.

